Public transport parks are always overcrowded, especially by matatus.Peak hours present even more danger of infection as vehicles move slowly due to traffic congestion. For the first time in centuries, humanity is fighting a common enemy – coronavirus disease. In Kenya, rural counties are bearing the brunt of what has been termed “the second wave of the pandemic”.
Even though Nairobi and Mombasa counties are still leading in infection rates, the disease is ravaging the rest of the nation. No doubt, the pandemic has disrupted our daily activities, ruined economies and livelihoods.



